Former President Jacob Zuma is returning to the High Court in Pietermaritzburg today. Zuma and French arms company Thales are accused of corruption, racketeering and money laundering linked to the arms deal. eNCA anchor Thulasizwe Simelane and senior reporter Siphamandla Goge are following this story. #DStv403 PIETERMARITZBURG - Former President Jacob Zuma is returning to the High Court in Pietermaritzburg on Tuesday. Zuma and the French arms company Thales are accused of corruption, racketeering and money laundering linked to the arms deal. READ: Zuma supporters plan march The former president has also applied for a special plea to have State prosecutor Advocate Billy Downer removed. He claims that his prosecution is political and Downer is biased.